.TH SM-REQ 1  "req " 
.SH NAME
req \- Manage requirements
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBreq\fR [\fB\-\-title\fR] [\fB\-\-status\fR] [\fB\-\-export\fR] [\fB\-\-to\fR] [\fB\-\-no\-template\fR] [\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR] <\fIPATH_OR_ID\fR> 
.SH DESCRIPTION
Manage requirements
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-\-title\fR \fI<TITLE>\fR
Title for new requirement
.TP
\fB\-\-status\fR \fI<STATUS>\fR
Update requirement status
.br

.br
\fIPossible values:\fR
.RS 14
.IP \(bu 2
open
.IP \(bu 2
in_progress
.IP \(bu 2
verified
.IP \(bu 2
rejected
.IP \(bu 2
deferred
.RE
.TP
\fB\-\-export\fR \fI<EXPORT>\fR
Export format (markdown, html, pdf, json)
.br

.br
\fIPossible values:\fR
.RS 14
.IP \(bu 2
markdown
.IP \(bu 2
html
.IP \(bu 2
pdf
.IP \(bu 2
json
.RE
.TP
\fB\-\-to\fR \fI<TO>\fR
Output path for export
.TP
\fB\-\-no\-template\fR
Skip template
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print help
.TP
<\fIPATH_OR_ID\fR>
Engagement path or requirement ID
